[Recent descriptions of norovirus-associated gastroenteritis have
focussed on fecal-oral and droplet-borne transmission of infection in
situations where disparate groups of people have been brought into
close proximity such as on cruise ships, or in schools, hospitals and
hotels. The above report and the 2 following reports suggest that
approximately 50 percent of all norovirus outbreaks (in the USA at
least) can be linked to ill food-service workers. - Mod.CP]

